uk.ac.ox.comlab.diadem.oxpath.core
Class PAATEval_Visitor

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ox.comlab.diadem.oxpath.parser.visitor.OXPathVisitorGenericAdaptor<PAATStateEvalIterative,OXPathType>
      uk.ac.ox.comlab.diadem.oxpath.core.PAATEval_Visitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
PAATEval_, OXPathParserVisitor, OXPathCache
public class PAATEval_Visitor
extends OXPathVisitorGenericAdaptor<PAATStateEvalIterative,OXPathType>
implements PAATEval_

Visitor encoding the eval_ function of the PAAT algorithm. Called by the PAATEvalVisitor, but wrapped in a dynamic proxy of a {PAATEval_Wrapper} object.

Author:
AndrewJSel

clear

public java.lang.Boolean clear(diadem.common.web.dom.DOMDocument page)
Clears all memoized data for the input DOMDocument. Will be overridden as long as a proxy object is used (should always be used for OXPath classes overridding this method).

Specified by:
clear in interface OXPathCache
Parameters:
page - DOMDocument we are removing all memoized results for, presumably because the page is being closed in PAAT
